20responsibilities.%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20back%2C%20and%20so%20is%20his%20signature%20foreign%20policy%20move%E2%80%94cutting%20the%20US%20off%20from%20some%20key%20global%20organisations.%20He%20has%2C%20just%20like%20during%20his%20first%20term%2C%20decided%20that%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%20doesn't%20deserve%20US%20funding%20anymore.%20His%20reason%20is%20the%20same%20as%20before%3A%20the%20WHO%20did%20not%20act%20right%20during%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20and%20that%20it's%20bent%20more%20favourably%20towards%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20contribution%20to%20WHO%20in%202024%20was%20%24950%20million.%20This%20was%20nearly%2015%25%20of%20the%20organisation's%20budget%2C%20making%20it%20the%20largest%20single%20donor%20out%20of%20194%20member%20countries.%20So%2C%20when%20Trump%20pulls%20out%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20a%20dent%E2%80%94it's%20a%20crater%20in%20the%20organisation's%20budget.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20is%20funded%20through%20two%20primary%20sources%3A%20assessed%20contributions%2C%20which%20are%20mandatory%20dues%20paid%20by%20the%20194%20member%20countries%2C%20calculated%20on%20factors%20like%20a%20country's%20wealth%20and%20population%2C%20and%20voluntary%20contributions%2C%20which%20come%20from%20member%20states%2C%20private%20individuals%2C%20philanthropic%20organisations%20and%20other%20partners.%20A%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20WHO's%20budget%20relies%20on%20voluntary%20contributions%2C%20chiefly%20the%20Bill%20%26amp%3B%20Melinda%20Gates%20Foundation%2C%20which%20provides%20substantial%20funding%20to%20support%20various%20global%20health%20initiatives.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Gates%20Foundation%20has%20pledged%20to%20continue%20to%20contribute%20to%20global%20health%20causes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Billion-Dollar%20Challenge%20To%20Trump%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%2C%20worried%20but%20not%20surprised%20like%20last%20time%2C%20has%20politely%20asked%20Trump%20to%20reconsider%20his%20decision.%20It%20says%20it%20%26quot%3Bplays%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20protecting%20the%20health%20and%20security%20of%20the%20world's%20people%2C%20including%20Americans%2C%20by%20addressing%20the%20root%20causes%20of%20disease%2C%20building%20stronger%20health%20systems%2C%20and%20detecting%2C%20preventing%20and%20responding%20to%20health%20emergencies%2C%20including%20disease%20outbreaks%2C%20often%20in%20dangerous%20places%20where%20others%20cannot%20go%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20global%20backlash%20to%20the%20US%20move.%20But%20this%20one%20should%20put%20the%20country%20to%20shame%3A%20a%20member%20of%20WHO%20staff%20has%20embarked%20on%20a%20campaign%20to%20raise%20%241%20billion%20through%20crowdfunding%E2%80%94just%20enough%20to%20cover%20what%20the%20US%20contributed%20in%202024.%20So%20far%2C%20donations%20have%20been%20only%20trickling%20in%E2%80%94ordinary%20citizens%20of%20the%20world%20are%20paying%20from%20%241%20to%20%244%2C000%20per%20person.%20It's%20a%20noble%20gesture%2C%20a%20show%20of%20defiance%20against%20Trump%2C%20but%20let's%20be%20honest.%20It's%20like%20climbing%20Mount%20Everest.%20The%20symbolism%2C%20though%2C%20is%20powerful.%20The%20message%20to%20Trump%20is%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20both%20applause%20and%20outrage.%20It%20vaccinated%20over%2090%25%20of%20children%20in%20Gaza%20against%20polio%E2%80%94commendable%20indeed%2C%20considering%20it%20accomplished%20the%20feat%20during%20the%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Gaza.%20It%20battled%20the%20Ebola%20virus%20in%20conflict%20zones%20where%20even%20armies%20feared%20to%20tread.%20It%20has%20led%20global%20vaccination%20drives%20that%20have%20saved%20millions%20of%20lives.%20But%20it%20has%20its%20share%20of%20shortcomings%20and%20failures%20too%3A%20it%20botched%20the%20early%20COVID-19%20response%2C%20hesitating%20to%20call%20out%20China%20when%20the%20virus%20first%20spread%2C%20it%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20bureaucratic%20delays%20that%20cost%20lives%20during%20major%20health%20crises%2C%20and%20though%20it%20has%20launched%20internal%20reforms%20since%20the%20end%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20they%20are%20not%20enough.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20Trump's%20executive%20order%20to%20cripple%20WHO%20financially%20to%20further%20his%20cause%20of%20pushing%20the%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20agenda%20may%20prove%20counterproductive.%20By%20walking%20away%20from%20global%20commitments%2C%20Trump%20might%20be%20winning%20cheers%20from%20his%20MAGA%20base%2C%20but%20he%20doesn't%20realise%20that%20when%20the%20next%20global%20health%20crisis%20hits%2C%20his%20country%20might%20find%20itself%20very%20much%20alone.%20And%20for%20a%20country%20that%20was%20once%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20free%20world%2C%20that's%20quite%20a%20downgrade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20what%20should%20be%20more%20worrying%20for%20the%20US%20is%20the%20possibility%20that%20Trump's%20action%20may%20just%20open%20up%20space%20for%20China%20to%20step%20in%20to%20fill%20the%20gap.%20Last%20time%20Trump%20pulled%20this%20stunt%2C%20China%20rushed%20in%2C%20pledging%20to%20increase%20its%20voluntary%20contributions%20to%20the%20WHO.%20This%20time%2C%20Beijing%20is%20still%20weighing%20its%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20Ever-Growing%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20exiting%20the%20WHO%20and%20other%20global%20agreements%20and%20institutions%20under%20Trump's%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20policy%20is%20going%20to%20create%20a%20power%20vacuum%2C%20which%20China%20is%20sure%20to%20quickly%20move%20to%20fill.%20If%20this%20trend%20continues%2C%20Beijing%20will%20feel%20that%20it%20would%20gain%20the%20ability%20to%20reshape%20international%20norms%2C%20setting%20rules%20that%20favour%20its%20economic%2C%20political%20and%20ideological%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere's%20proof%20to%20back%20this.%20But%20first%20let's%20look%20at%20which%20treaties%20and%20organisations%20Trump%20got%20out%20of%20during%20his%20first%20term%20that%20led%20to%20the%20US%20retreating%20from%20global%20leadership%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWorld%20Health%20Organization%C2%A0(2020)%3A%20The%20US%20left%20it%20amid%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20being%20too%20China-centric%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EParis%20Climate%20Accord%20(2017)%3A%20The%20US%20claimed%20that%20it%20unfairly%20burdened%20the%20US%20while%20allowing%20China%20to%20pollute.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIran%20Nuclear%20Deal%20(JCPOA)%20(2018)%3A%20America's%20exit%20led%20to%20Iran's%20renewed%20nuclear%20activity%20and%20increased%20West%20Asia%20tensions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETrans-Pacific%20Partnership%20(TPP)%20(2017)%3A%20The%20US%20cancelled%20a%20major%20trade%20pact%20designed%20to%20counter%20China's%20dominance%20in%20Asia.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUNESCO%20%26amp%3B%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20(2018)%3A%20The%20American%20withdrawal%20was%20due%20to%20claims%20of%20bias%20against%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EArms%20Control%20Treaties%3A%20The%20US%20withdrew%20from%20the%20INF%20Treaty%20with%20Russia%2C%20increasing%20global%20arms%20race%20risks%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENATO%20%26amp%3B%20G7%20Threats%3A%20Trump%20repeatedly%20threatened%20to%20withdraw%20from%20NATO%2C%20weakening%20confidence%20in%20the%20alliance%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20these%20exits%20did%20not%20necessarily%20weaken%20the%20organisations%20themselves%2C%20but%20they%20certainly%20led%20to%20massive%20uncertainties.%20Some%20might%20argue%20it%20reduced%20US%20influence%20and%20allowed%20China%20to%20step%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20fill%20the%20leadership%20vacuum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20China%20Gain%20From%20US%20Withdrawals%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Trump%20cut%20WHO%20funding%20in%202020%2C%20China%20stepped%20up%2C%20committing%20%2450%20million%20more%20to%20fill%20the%20gap.%20Though%20the%20increased%20amount%20was%20far%20below%20the%20US%20contributions%2C%20it%20allowed%20Beijing%20to%20increase%20its%20influence%20in%20the%20organisation%2C%20block%20investigations%20into%20COVID-19%20origins%2C%20and%20promote%20its%20vaccines%20globally.%20When%20Trump%20withdrew%20from%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Accord%2C%20China%20became%20the%20climate%20leader%20in%20climate%20discussions.%20Beijing%20now%20portrays%20itself%20as%20greener%20than%20the%20US%2C%20despite%20being%20the%20world's%20largest%20polluter.%20Similarly%2C%20after%20Trump%20unilaterally%20left%20the%20Iran%20Nuclear%20Deal%2C%20China%20strengthened%20ties%20with%20Tehran.%20It%20also%20increased%20oil%20imports%20from%20Iran%20and%20expanded%20economic%20ties%2C%20undermining%20US%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20when%20Trump%20withdrew%2C%20rather%20foolishly%2C%20from%20the%20Trans-Pacific%20Partnership%20(TPP)%2C%20China%20joined%20the%20Regional%20Comprehensive%20Economic%20Partnership%20(RCEP)%2C%20now%20the%20world's%20largest%20trade%20pact%E2%80%94without%20the%20US%20being%20a%20part%20of%20it.%20The%20result%20is%20that%20the%20Asian%20countries%20now%20trade%20more%20with%20China%20than%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%20Sets%20The%20Agenda%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20secured%20key%20leadership%20roles%20in%20UN%20agencies%20such%20as%20the%20International%20Telecommunication%20Union%20(ITU)%2C%20which%20governs%20internet%20standards.%20It%20uses%20these%20positions%20to%20push%20for%20global%20acceptance%20of%20Chinese%20tech%20models%2C%20such%20as%20surveillance-based%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20Trump%20withdraws%20from%20global%20agreements%20and%20institutions%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20campaign%2C%20the%20weaker%20it%20makes%20his%20country%2C%20because%20someone%20else%20takes%20its%20leadership%20role.%20That%20someone%20else%2C%20in%20this%20case%2C%20will%20be%20none%20other%20than%20China.%20By%20enhancing%20its%20contributions%20to%20a%20large%20extent%2C%20it%20will%20surely%20set%20global%20economic%20rules%2C%20trade%20investment%20policies%20favouring%20state-owned%20enterprises%2C%20and%20Chinese%20dominance.%20It%20could%20control%20global%20health%20governance%20by%20prioritising%20Chinese%20interests%2C%20influencing%20pandemic%20response%20and%20vaccine%20policies.%20It%20will%20try%20to%20shape%20digital%20and%20internet%20rules%20by%20expanding%20China's%20alleged%20authoritarian%20%26quot%3Bcyber%20sovereignty%26quot%3B%20model%2C%20limiting%20online%20freedoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20will%20expand%20military%20alliances%20by%20strengthening%20BRICS%20and%20China-led%20military%20partnerships%20to%20counter%20US%20alliances.%20It%20will%20try%20to%20dominate%20climate%20policies%20by%20controlling%20carbon%20markets%20and%20green%20technologies%20while%20holding%20the%20West%20accountable%20for%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%20Can%20Be%20Checkmated%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20still%20time%20for%20influential%20countries%20like%20India%20and%20European%20nations%20to%20step%20up%2C%20support%20the%20WHO%20more%20and%20prevent%20China%20from%20assuming%20a%20dominant%20decision-making%20role.%20Rather%20than%20allowing%20Beijing%20to%20expand%20its%20influence%20unchecked%2C%20member%20countries%20must%20collectively%20address%20WHO's%20funding%20and%20governance%20challenges.%20Mid-sized%20economies%20like%20India%20and%20Brazil%2C%20along%20with%20developed%20nations%2C%20such%20as%20the%20UK%2C%20Germany%20and%20France%2C%20should%20increase%20their%20contributions%20to%20maintain%20a%20balanced%20and%20effective%20WHO.%20The%20organisation's%20past%20success%20in%20eradicating%20smallpox%E2%80%94one%20of%20humanity's%20greatest%20achievements%E2%80%94demonstrates%20that%20global%20health%20cooperation%20can%20transcend%20political%20divides%20to%20protect%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20US%2C%20I%20wonder%2C%20does%20MAGA%20truly%20make%20America%20stronger%2C%20or%20does%20it%20isolate%20the%20country%20while%20China%20fills%20the%20void%20in%20global%20institutions%3F%20With%20each%20withdrawal%E2%80%94from%20WHO%20to%20climate%20agreements%20and%20beyond%E2%80%94Trump's%20America%20retreats%20from%20leadership%2C%20leaving%20a%20power%20vacuum%20that%20Beijing%20is%20eager%20to%20exploit.%20Are%20we%20heading%20towards%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20Alone%26quot%3B%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739450280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2F8nh87li_trump_625x300_21_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhow-china-is-rushing-to-fill-the-gaps-trump-leaves-behind-7702536%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20each%20withdrawalfrom%20WHO%20to%20climate%20agreements%20and%20beyondTrumps%20America%20retreats%20from%20leadership%2C%20leaving%20a%20power%20vacuum%20that%20Beijing%20is%20eager%20to%20exploit.%20Are%20we%20heading%20towards%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20Alone%26quot%3B%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Today%20is%20the%20big%20one'%3A%20Trump's%20'reciprocal%20tariffs'%20post%20before%20meeting%20with%20PM%20Modi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739450045000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118216283