d%20my%20job%20with%20the%20postal%20service%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20title%20of%20my%20position%20was%20%26quot%3Bletter%20carrier.%26quot%3B%20On%20a%20typical%20day%2C%20I'd%20start%20at%207%20a.m.%2C%20then%20have%20about%20one-and-a-half%20to%20two%20hours%20to%20process%20and%20organize%20the%20mail.%20After%20that%2C%20I'd%20leave%20the%20station%20and%20deliver%20mail%20for%20about%20six%20hours%20before%20coming%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20pretty%20simple%20job%2C%20it%20was%20just%20physically%20demanding.%20After%20you%20finished%20your%20delivery%2C%20you'd%20be%20able%20to%20go%20home%2C%20and%20sometime%2C%20I'd%20finish%20quite%20early%20in%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20best%20thing%20about%20being%20a%20postman%20was%20that%20you're%20out%20in%20nature%20all%20day%20exercising.%20Every%20day%2C%20I%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalking-10000-steps-for-health-not-science-based-in-marketing-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewalk%20around%2015%2C000%20steps%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20at%20work%2C%20often%20somewhere%20between%20six%20to%20seven%20and%20a%20half%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20liked%20the%20social%20aspect%20of%20it.%20I%20got%20to%20know%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20customers%2C%20and%20I'd%20call%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20friends.%20When%20you%20think%20about%20it%2C%20I%20got%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-adding-low-paying-healthcare-retail-jobs-high-wages-scarce-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecent%20wage%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20exercise%20and%20socialize.%20It%20was%20a%20really%20good%20gig.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20so%20much%20fun%20being%20a%20postman%2C%20but%20the%20last%20six%20months%20were%20the%20hardest.%20I%20saw%20the%20business%20model%20changing%2C%20and%20I%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20move%20on.%20I'd%20also%20paid%20as%20much%20into%20my%20pension%20as%20I%20could%2C%20so%20it%20made%